PS. there should be the following line:
task.close();
task = null; // insert this line
resp.getWriter().write(baos.toString());

Issue: when BIRT is integrated into a system such as Tiles where BIRT is used as a tile, you are unable to use the output stream as it has already been opened and written to by the parent servlet. Instead, you must use the Writer.

The following will throw an exception:
renderOptions.setOutputStream(response.getOutputSteam());

Current workaround:
Instead use:
ByteArrayOutputStream baos = new ByteArrayOutputStream(2048);
renderOptions.setOutputStream(baos);
task.setRenderOptions(renderOptions);
task.run();
response.getWriter().write(baos.toString());

Suggested fix:
Add method: renderOptions.setWriter(Writer);

